Package ru.tinkoff.qa.neptune.selenium.content.management

Annotation Interface BrowserUrlVariable

@Retention(RUNTIME) @Target({FIELD,METHOD}) @Repeatable(BrowserUrlVariables.class) public @interface BrowserUrlVariable

  • Optional Element Summary

    Optional Elements
    Modifier and Type
    Optional Element
    Description
    String
    method
     
    String
    name
     
    boolean
    toEncodeForQueries
    Should be value url-encoded or not for queries of URLs.

  • Element Details

    • name

      String name
      Returns:
      name of a URL-variable. When value is empty then name of an annotated field is used.
      Default:
      ""

    • toEncodeForQueries

      boolean toEncodeForQueries
      Should be value url-encoded or not for queries of URLs.
      Default:
      true

    • method

      String method
      Returns:
      name of a method whose non-null returned value be should used as a value of the URL-variable to navigate in browser. It has sense when type of a marked field differs from primitive/wrappers/string. This method should not have any parameter and it should not be static
      Default:
      ""
